  "prompt": "What does \"last activity\" mean on Skype?",
  "response": "On Skype, \"last activity\" refers to the most recent time a user was actively using the application. This indicator helps you see when a contact was last online, which can be useful for determining their availability for communication. The feature may show a specific time or a relative time frame (like \"last seen 2 hours ago\"). Keep in mind that privacy settings may allow users to hide their last activity, so not all contacts will have this information visible.",
